Each field serves a purpose:
- **`isError: true`** — signals an error at the protocol level (MCP `CallToolResult`)
- **`errorCategory: "business"`** — tells Claude this is a policy issue, not a bug
- **`isRetryable: false`** — tells Claude to escalate, not retry
- **`customer_friendly_message`** — a safe message Claude can relay to the customer

Without these fields, Claude gets a generic "error" and has to guess whether to retry, escalate, or apologize. Structured errors enable intelligent recovery.

