### Step 4: Add allowed_tools restriction profiles

In CI/CD or restricted contexts, `allowed_tools` limits which tools Claude Code can use. A review-only profile drops Bash and Write so Claude Code can read and search but never execute commands or modify files.

```python
# ============================================================
# PART 4: ALLOWED_TOOLS RESTRICTION
# ============================================================

CI_PROFILES = {
    "review_only": {
        "description": "Code review -- read but never modify",
        "allowed_tools": ["Read", "Grep", "Glob"],
        "blocked": ["Bash", "Write", "Edit"],
        "reason": "Reviewer should never execute code or "
                  "modify files in CI",
    },
    "test_runner": {
        "description": "Run tests and report results",
        "allowed_tools": ["Read", "Grep", "Glob", "Bash"],
        "blocked": ["Write", "Edit"],
        "reason": "Can execute tests but should never modify "
                  "source files",
    },
    "full_access": {
        "description": "Local development -- all tools",
        "allowed_tools": ["Read", "Write", "Edit",
                          "Grep", "Glob", "Bash"],
        "blocked": [],
        "reason": "Developer workstation, full trust",
    },
}


def attempt_tool(tool_name, allowed_tools):
    """Check if a tool is allowed under a restriction profile."""
    if tool_name in allowed_tools:
        return {"tool": tool_name, "status": "ALLOWED"}
    return {"tool": tool_name, "status": "BLOCKED",
            "error": f"'{tool_name}' not in allowed_tools"}
```

