**B.** Add few-shot examples showing correct extraction
**C.** Increase max_tokens so the model has more room to be precise
**D.** Add custom semantic validation (cross-field checks) and make vendor_id nullable to prevent fabrication

**Correct: D.** tool_use + JSON schema eliminates syntax errors but NOT semantic errors (wrong sums, fabricated values). Custom validation catches cross-field issues, and nullable fields prevent fabrication. **Why not A:** A stricter JSON schema only enforces structural rules -- it cannot validate that line items sum correctly or detect fabricated values. **Why not B:** Few-shot examples can improve extraction quality probabilistically but cannot guarantee cross-field consistency the way programmatic validation can. **Why not C:** max_tokens controls output length, not extraction accuracy.

