**C.** `{"type": "tool", "name": "extract_invoice"}` -- always use the invoice tool
**D.** Don't use tool_choice -- let Claude figure it out

**Correct: B.** `"any"` forces Claude to call one of the available tools -- guaranteeing structured output -- while letting it pick the right schema based on document content. **Why not A:** `"auto"` might return text instead of calling a tool, which defeats the purpose of structured extraction. **Why not C:** Forcing the invoice tool on a receipt produces wrong results. **Why not D:** Without `tool_choice`, Claude might return text instead of structured data.

